 the history of the political ecology and shows how an ecological governmentality that understands governing as regulating, thus being in conflict with neo-liberalism, came into being and how potent it is.  afunded by Exzellenzcluster »Kulturelle Grundlagen von Integration« der Universität Konstanz  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEnvironmental policy. 0aPolitical ecology. 0aSustainabilityxGovernment policy. 4aGouvernementalität. 4aKultur. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMacht. 4aMichel Foucault. 4aNatur. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aUmweltpolitik. 4aÖkologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCultural Theory.  aCulture.  aEcology.  aEnvironmental Policy.  aGovernmentality.  aMichel Foucault.  aNature.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aPower.2 aExzellenzcluster »Kulturelle Grundlagen von Integration« der Universität Konstanzefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2018 Part 2z978311076667708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839444702zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839444702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839444702/original  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-076667-7  DG Plus PP Package 2018 Part 2b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME 